 the economic growth, social sanctuary, and environmental transformations of the twentieth century. In ways both material and symbolic, small human acts have overlapped with evolving systems of power to create this bustling metropolis. A People's History of SFO ends by addressing the climate crisis, as sea levels rise and threaten SFO itself on the edge of San Francisco Bay.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / West (AK, CA, CO, HI, ID, MT, NV, UT, WY).2bisacsh  aaircraft.  aairport.  aaviation.  abay area.  aboeing.  acalifornia.  aclimate crisis.  acolonial.  aconstruction.  aconsumer.  across continental.  adevelopment.  aflying.  aglobal.  aplane.  asan francisco.  atravel.  auntold history.  awest coast.  aworld wide.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520977075?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520977075423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520977075/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY